works.description: When it comes to car auctions, rare Ferraris have always turned out to be the record breakers. Now, four magnificent Ferraris are up for grabs at Bonhams’ sale of Collectors’ Motor Cars and Automobilia at the Royal Air Force Museum, Hendon on April 11, 2011. The cars come from a private collection, and include a 1999 Ferrari F50 Barchetta, a 1985 Ferrari 288GTO Berlinetta, a 1990 Ferrari F40 Berlinetta and a 2003 Ferrari 360 Challenge Stradale. The four cars together are expected to bring in more than £1 million (about $1.4 million)
